The paper deals with a problem in online matching, which is a classic topic in computer science. The problem is motivated by applications such as e-commerce, online advertising, and ride-sharing, which are related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the definition of competitive ratio in the stochastic setting, which is related to game theory (cs.GT). The paper presents a new algorithm for the problem, which involves analyzing the performance of the algorithm, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and learning theory (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of linear programming formulations, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
